Karl,

I don't have an answer to your problem but I want to call your attention
to a related problem which is causing me a bit of pain.  If you are
going to use those wildcard MX RRs please be prepared to handle all of
the mail that will come to you as a result of them including bogus hosts
in those domains.  There are some large mail handlers who use wildcards
and proceed to send mail for bogus hosts off to europe or New Jersey.
Eventually the mail does fail after a long trip around the Internet or
through uucp-land.  It would be much better for everyone if the MXer
dumped the mail right away.

/dan

